				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Combat and Combos
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1754423">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							The first few days I loved elementalists that placed down combo fields for me to shoot through, although lately it seems like the most common effect my arrows are causing is &quot;condition loss&quot;, which I think is a result of necromancer or guardian combo fields.<br />
<br />
In the beta, engineers in pvp used to drop a smoke field and then immediately set off a blast, which gave their team mass stealth while someone else also set up a team swiftness. I think engineers had their blast finishers removed as a result though.<br />
<br />
It's generally easier to use someone else's. I've discovered a few I can do myself though. At first I was using a torch offhand to create a ring of fire, and then throwing projectiles through it. Rangers only have two finishers, one being a whirling finisher, which honestly I was not impressed with. It was hard to determine if it worked, let alone how effective it was. <br />
<br />
They also have a leap finisher on greatsword, which is pretty... great. It's supposed to be a gap closer, but I can drop a fire trap in melee range before using it and get &quot;fire shield/armor&quot; which I believe does additional fire damage. I can also drop a healing spring and get an aoe heal at the same time, and later I will be able to get a frost combo field.<br />
<br />
I actually created a chart/list in a txt file keeping track of all the field and finisher abilities, as part of the process of me trying to pick a class weeks/months ago. Guardians and Warriors seem to have the most finishers. I think Elementalists had the most fields, can't remember.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
