				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Combat and Combos
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1754558">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							The most common thing I can do as a mage is Lava Font -&gt; Arcane Wave, which sets off Might x3 for everyone in the area? I think? I know I get Mightx3, and lemme tell you, I hit my heal glyph (+1 Might) and things just explode.<br />
<br />
It wouldn't surprise me that mages have the most fields; Fire, Lightning, Water, Ice, I think? Plus a couple of blasts and a projectile finisher. I'm having a ball figuring out various combos. My favorite so far in solo play is wielding dual daggers, starting in Lightning Attunement: Ride the Lighting -&gt; Updraft -&gt; [Atunement swap: Fire] Burning Speed -&gt; Arcane Wave -&gt; Glyph of EH (Mightx4) -&gt; [Attunement swap: earth] Earthquake -&gt; Churning Earth.<br />
<br />
It's really tricky to pull off the entire sequence, and I usually have to abort halfway through. When it clicks though, BOOM!<br />
<br />
I don't see a lot of Shadow fields around. I'm not all that familiar with the Necro class and what they can bring to the table, other than the freakiest pets imaginable.
						</blockquote>
